---
import PolicyPageLayout from '../../layouts/PolicyPageLayout.astro';

const updatedAt = new Date('2026-07-22');
const sections = [
  { depth: 2, slug: 'who-operates-this-site', text: 'Who operates this site' },
  { depth: 2, slug: 'what-evidique-collects', text: 'What evidique collects' },
  { depth: 2, slug: 'cloudflare-hosting-data', text: 'Cloudflare hosting data' },
  { depth: 2, slug: 'cookies-accounts-and-analytics', text: 'Cookies, accounts, and analytics' },
  { depth: 2, slug: 'on-device-search', text: 'On-device search' },
  { depth: 2, slug: 'email-communications', text: 'Email communications' },
  { depth: 2, slug: 'external-and-affiliate-links', text: 'External and affiliate links' },
  { depth: 2, slug: 'legal-bases', text: 'Legal bases' },
  {
    depth: 2,
    slug: 'retention-and-international-processing',
    text: 'Retention and international processing',
  },
  { depth: 2, slug: 'your-privacy-rights', text: 'Your privacy rights' },
  { depth: 2, slug: 'children', text: 'Children' },
  { depth: 2, slug: 'security-and-changes', text: 'Security and changes' },
  { depth: 2, slug: 'contact', text: 'Contact' },
];
---

<PolicyPageLayout
  title="Privacy policy"
  description="What data this static publication handles, which services may process it, and the choices available to you."
  kicker="Less collection, less explaining"
  recordLabel="Privacy notice"
  {updatedAt}
  {sections}
  highlights={[
    'No evidique accounts, comment system, contact form, or analytics script.',
    'Search runs locally in your browser against a static index.',
    'Cloudflare processes technical request data to deliver and protect the site.',
  ]}
>
  <h2 id="who-operates-this-site">Who operates this site</h2>
  <p>
    evidique is an independent publication operated by Ethan Miller. For privacy questions or rights
    requests, email <a href="mailto:x771364026@gmail.com">x771364026@gmail.com</a>.
  </p>
  <p>
    This policy covers visits to evidique and direct email exchanges with the editor. It does not
    control the privacy practices of software vendors or other sites we link to.
  </p>

  <h2 id="what-evidique-collects">What evidique collects</h2>
  <p>
    The site is statically generated and does not maintain its own visitor database. evidique does
    not ask visitors to create an account, post a comment, submit a web form, or provide payment
    details.
  </p>
  <p>
    If you email us, we receive the address, message, attachments, and any information you choose to
    include. Avoid sending passwords, payment-card numbers, or other sensitive information.
  </p>

  <h2 id="cloudflare-hosting-data">Cloudflare hosting data</h2>
  <p>
    Cloudflare hosts, delivers, and protects the site. When your browser requests a page, Cloudflare
    may process technical information such as IP address, request time, requested URL, browser and
    device details, network identifiers, and security signals needed to serve content and detect
    abuse.
  </p>
  <p>
    Cloudflare controls its infrastructure logs and retention practices under its own privacy terms.
    evidique does not copy those request logs into a separate audience database.
  </p>

  <h2 id="cookies-accounts-and-analytics">Cookies, accounts, and analytics</h2>
  <p>
    evidique currently sets no first-party advertising or analytics cookies and runs no analytics,
    behavioral profiling, or session-replay script. There is no login or newsletter submission
    endpoint.
  </p>
  <p>
    Cloudflare may use strictly necessary security mechanisms when required to protect the service.
    If evidique later adds analytics, subscriptions, or optional cookies, this policy and the
    relevant consent controls will be updated before those features are enabled.
  </p>

  <h2 id="on-device-search">On-device search</h2>
  <p>
    Site search uses Pagefind. Your browser downloads a static search index and performs the query
    on your device. evidique does not receive or store the words you type into the search box.
  </p>

  <h2 id="email-communications">Email communications</h2>
  <p>
    We use email information to read and answer corrections, questions, access offers, and other
    messages. We do not add a sender to a marketing list merely because they contacted us.
  </p>
  <p>
    Messages may be retained while they remain useful for the conversation, editorial record,
    dispute handling, security, or legal obligations. You may request deletion, subject to records
    we must reasonably keep.
  </p>

  <h2 id="external-and-affiliate-links">External and affiliate links</h2>
  <p>
    Links may take you to a vendor, documentation site, or affiliate destination. Once you leave
    evidique, the third party may collect data or set cookies under its own policy. Review those
    terms before providing personal information or making a purchase.
  </p>
  <p>
    evidique does not sell personal information and does not share it for cross-context behavioral
    advertising. More detail about commercial links appears in the
    <a href="/affiliate-disclosure/">affiliate disclosure</a>.
  </p>

  <h2 id="legal-bases">Legal bases</h2>
  <p>
    Where data-protection law requires a legal basis, technical delivery and security processing is
    based on the legitimate interest in operating a safe, reliable publication. Email processing is
    based on responding to your request, taking steps you ask us to take, or the same legitimate
    interest in maintaining editorial records.
  </p>
  <p>
    Consent will be requested before introducing optional processing where consent is legally
    required. You may withdraw consent for future processing at any time.
  </p>

  <h2 id="retention-and-international-processing">Retention and international processing</h2>
  <p>
    evidique keeps personal information only as long as reasonably necessary for the purpose
    described above, including security, editorial accountability, and legal obligations. Hosting
    providers may process technical data in countries other than your own using the safeguards
    described in their terms.
  </p>

  <h2 id="your-privacy-rights">Your privacy rights</h2>
  <p>
    Depending on where you live, you may have rights to request access, correction, deletion,
    restriction, portability, or objection to certain processing. You may also have the right to
    complain to a local data-protection authority.
  </p>
  <p>
    California residents may request information about covered personal information and may request
    correction or deletion where applicable. evidique will not discriminate against you for making a
    valid privacy request. We may need enough information to verify the request and protect another
    person's data.
  </p>

  <h2 id="children">Children</h2>
  <p>
    evidique is written for adults choosing professional software and is not directed to children
    under 13. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children. If you believe a child
    has sent us personal information, contact us so it can be reviewed and deleted where
    appropriate.
  </p>

  <h2 id="security-and-changes">Security and changes</h2>
  <p>
    We use a static architecture and Cloudflare's delivery controls to reduce the amount of visitor
    data held by evidique. No internet service can promise perfect security, so please use care when
    sending information by email.
  </p>
  <p>
    This policy may change when the site, providers, or legal requirements change. Material updates
    will appear on this page with a revised effective date before or when the new practice begins.
  </p>

  <h2 id="contact">Contact</h2>
  <p>
    Send privacy questions and rights requests to
    <a href="mailto:x771364026@gmail.com">x771364026@gmail.com</a>. Include the request, the country
    or state relevant to it, and enough context for us to respond without sending unnecessary
    sensitive information.
  </p>
</PolicyPageLayout>
